<zk>
	<zscript><![CDATA[
		import java.util.HashMap;
		java.util.Map noAuto = new HashMap();
		noAuto.put("autoPluginButtons", Boolean.FALSE);
	]]></zscript>
	<vlayout>
		<label value="ZK-5992 — auto toolbar buttons + autoPluginButtons opt-out"/>
		<label multiline="true">
What this page shows: the auto-inserted toolbar button feature and its opt-out.
Both editors enable the same plugin (table); only the button insertion differs.

How to verify (compare the two toolbars):
1. tbAuto (plugins="table"): the table toolbar button IS auto-inserted.
2. tbNoAuto (plugins="table", config.autoPluginButtons=false): the plugin still LOADS
   (trumbowyg.table.js is requested) but NO table button is inserted.
3. Both: trumbowyg.table.js is requested only once (shared, de-duplicated).
		</label>

		<!-- default: the table plugin's toolbar button is auto-inserted -->
		<tbeditor id="tbAuto" plugins="table" width="500px"/>

		<!-- opt-out: the plugin still loads, but no button is auto-inserted -->
		<tbeditor id="tbNoAuto" plugins="table" config="${noAuto}" width="500px"/>
	</vlayout>
</zk>
